The paper deals with security threats to unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and proposes a mathematical framework for analyzing and mitigating GPS spoofing attacks on UAVs. This involves modeling the optimal routes that UAVs will adopt to reach their destinations, and developing a countermeasure mechanism based on cooperative localization. The paper also formulates a dynamic Stackelberg game to model the interactions between a GPS spoofer and a drone operator. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
